  "texts": [
    "Then since (a, b) ⊆ O ′, we have M, O ′ ⊮ ♢ ▷ χ by the truth clause for ♢ ▷ given R-down (recall § 2.4).",
    "To prove the claim, suppose (a, b)R ▷ σ.",
    "Since χ M = ↓σ O, M, σ ⊩ χ only if σ ⊆ σ O.",
    "Suppose for reductio that σ ⊆ σ O, so there is an ⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ ∈ σ such that (a ′, b ′) ⊆ O.",
    "Together ⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ ∈ σ and (a, b)R ▷ σ imply (a, b) ∩ (a ′, b ′) ̸ = ∅ by the definition of R ▷."
  ],
